<chapter xml:id="ch-chapter-title" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Introduction to Chemistry and The Scientific Method</title>

    <introduction>
        <p>
            In our first section, we will begin to develop our understanding of chemistry and take a closer look at how scientists approach understanding the world around us.
        </p>

        <objectives>
            <p>
                In this module, our goals are to:
            </p>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    Develop an understanding of chemistry.
                </li>

                <li>
                    Define the steps of the scientific method.
                </li>

                <li>
                    Recognize the difference between a scientific theory and scientific law.
                </li>

                <li>
                    Distinguish between qualitative and quantitative observations.
                </li>

                <li>
                    Classify independent, dependent, and controlled variables.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </objectives>

        <figure xml:id="intro-chemistry">
            <image source="chapters/ch01-introduction/images/beaker.jpg" width="60%" >
                <description>
                    An assortment of colorful liquid filled test tubes in a beaker.
                </description>
            </image>
            <caption>An assortment of colorful liquid filled test tubes in a beaker.</caption>
        </figure>
    </introduction>
